[Name] dvgrab
[Summary] A utility to save video data from a Mini-DV Video Camcorder.
[License] GNU General Public License (GPL)
[Description] dvgrab receives audio and video data from a digital camcorder via an IEEE 1394 (widely known as FireWire) link and stores them into an AVI file. It features autosplit of long video sequences into several files, and supports saving the data as raw frames, AVI type 1, AVI type 2, and image files.
[Homepage] http://kino.schirmacher.de/
